a-size-base: One of my cats favorite treats
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
a-size-base 3: I wanted to find a soft treat for my cats that was healthy and had cranberry in it that my cats would both eat. That is tricky nowadays having two cats with different tastebuds. However ever since I’ve found this on a pet store shelf I will search until I can get my hands on it! I only can find it online now but it makes me feel better that my cats are getting a healthy treat in them that hopefully will help prevent issues down the line.
a-alert-heading: There was a problem loading comments right now. Please try again later.

a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2021
a-size-base 3: So, the super finicky felines that rule the house can, coincidentally, be super finicky about their treats. One will throw up if he gets more than 2-3 at one time, another looks at them and gives me a blank look as if asking “What did you just try to pawn off on me?”, and then there’s the third one that is all-the-treats-all-the-time. So I have a hard time finding treats that they will all like or at least two out of three. So what did they think of these?Smell (that’s mostly me): On the mild side. Didn’t really smell like chicken to me.Hard/soft: Very soft. Two of the cats seemed to eat them okay, but the one that’s missing most of her teeth had trouble with them.Taste (that’s them): they seemed a bit dubious and I think that might be down to the mild smell. While they did eat them, the toothless one was the slower of the three to jump on them.Overall: I like that this product is made in the USA and it’s for all life stages since ours range from 4-11yo. I’ve also found that they do seem to enjoy cranberry when it’s in their foods, which is always a bonus for me (and them). And at the listed price, it’s about on par with other similar products out there. In looking at the brand, I also see that there’s other flavor options, which I intend to investigate.

a-size-base 3: We have six cats and Temptations are their kitty crack of choice, but these far-healthier Naked Biteables are beloved by Woodrow and Wolfie, brothers who are prone to minor but regular UTIs. These treats contain cranberry and that's exactly what they need in their diet to make sure they don't develop problems.While I do add a powder UTI supplement to their food at meals, I love that they come running for these treats several times a day as well. It helps keep them safe and happy.Not all of the other four like them but that's fine. The two that benefit most absolutely love them and I love giving them to them.

a-size-base: They were great for a few days, but not anymore.
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2021
a-size-base 3: Based on both cats loving the purple furball soft-treats made by the same company, I thought I'd give the health soft-treats a try. At first, both cats would devour them just like the other kind. However, after a few days, the pickier of the two would begin to vomit after eating a few of the health treats, and even the other one would no longer inhale them like he used to.2 days later, the fussy eater will not touch the health treats at all, and will also no longer touch the furball treats - shame, thought I'd finally found something she'd like, but I guess it was not meant to be. Might give it a few days and see if she wants to try at least the furball treats again, but it does look like the health treats are a lost cause for both cats.
